<TITLE> Govt official shot in car in broad daylight </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com)Forty-year-old Fazle Rabbi Munshi, executive engineer of the family planning directorate, was shot through the window of his car in the capital's busy Tejgaon area within yards of a police station on Tuesday morning. Police said Fazle Rabbi was on his way to work from his Tejkunipara residence, when he was shot in front of the Imperial Guest House near Tejgaon Police Station at around 9:20am. "The assailants shot at him through the open window of his car that was stuck in a traffic jam. He was hit in the buttock," Tejgaon police chief Mahbubur Rahman told bdnews24.com. One of the two men, who waylaid and shot the engineer, was caught and arrested by the police. The other escaped. The detained suspect, named 'Rakib', in his early 20s, claimed he and his companion were paid Tk 10,000 to shoot Engineer Fazle Rabbi, the police chief said. The injured engineer was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Police speculated the incident might have occurred in connection with a public tender. Rahman said they were investigating the shooting. bdnews24
